<paragraph blockId="11.[112,648,787,1098]" box="[115,243,787,813]" pageId="11" pageNumber="800">VARIABILITY</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[112,648,787,1098]" pageId="11" pageNumber="800">The first thecate internode of hydrocladia usually bears two mesial inferior nematothecae: one near the basal node and other below the hydrotheca but with its margin reaching the base. Only the basal nematothecae is placed on a distinct swelling. Rest of thecate internodes with only one mesial inferior nematotheca, except in cases of damage and further regeneration where two nematothecae are possible.</paragraph>
